<p>I would like to create a "Restore in-App" button because it is required by Apple. I am using Parse for my iAP product and I used this code to do that:</p>  <pre><code>PFPurchase.buyProduct("iapbanner", block: { (error:NSError!) -&gt; Void in             if error != nil {                 let alert = UIAlertController(title: "Errore", message: error?.localizedDescription, preferredStyle: UIAlertControllerStyle.Alert)                 alert.addAction(UIAlertAction(title: "Ok", style: UIAlertActionStyle.Default, handler: nil))                 self.presentViewController(alert, animated: true, completion: nil)             } else {                 self.opzioniTableView.reloadData()             }         }) </code></pre>  <p>This works fine. Though, in the Parse's documentation it's not mentioned how to restore your iAp so I'm asking you.</p>